14:
Well, yeah. It was good!
You've hardly touched yours though.
21: You still worryin' about that girl?
23: She's not Stella. Not even close.
26: But when I first met Stella, she was—
36:
Long shall be the tale of Onyudo's 
rampage! Gather ye, gather all who 
would dare challenge him!
40: I feel like we've been in this situation before...
46:
Sheesh. All right, you three, 
I'll play with you. 
I just finished dinner. Maybe I'll have 
some Onyudo for dessert! GRAAAR!
53: Nimbus, no! We won't taste good!
58:
Ahaha, and so ends the tale of Onyudo. 
I tried to warn them you would not be 
so easily deceived.
62:
It has been too long since last we met. 
The children came to play with you.
72: So, what brings you to Starview? Just chaperoning?
76:
Yes. The kits have been visiting me 
rather often of late. These three—Awa, 
Hie, and Mugi—are always happy to 
have a playmate.
80:
So you used the diviners' precious 
World Flipper to take the kids out on 
a field trip? How'd you manage to run 
that by Suizen?
83:
Word for word, we ran past him. Under 
the cover of night, naturally.
92:
Suizen is no longer a stranger to us. 
I am sure he will understand.
93: I will admit, I too was curious.
95:
I have only but arrived, and yet...
Starview is as wonderous a village 
as I could have dreamed.
98:
Heh. Guess it's not half bad. I used to 
think I was the only talkin' beast out 
there, and look where we are now!
101: There's never a dull day 'round here.
106:
It is with that in mind, I approach you 
with a humble request.
109:
If I may, I would like to join you here in 
Starview Village.
118:
I understand this is sudden, 
but I implore you to consider it.
124:
There's nothing to consider! You're 
always welcome here, Soushiro!
128:
Yeah, and drop the formalities.
I'll show you the training room later. 
You've gotta show me that crazy 
swordsmanship of yours again!
136:
What a sight to behold
—a sky of worlds instead of stars.
138:
Entire worlds...
Even the darkest clouds would fail to 
mask such powerful light.
